<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6833&amp;p=65946#p65946"><![CDATA[
I blame Ronaldo.<br /><br />On a more serious note, similar prices (though not as inflated, but close!) are seen in post-socialist countries in the EU, like Sweden.  This is especially the case for technological/electronic devices.  There, it's actually cheaper to buy something in the US + pay international shipping rates + pay VAT than to buy it local.<br /><br />Though, in their case, I believe the markup is a result of vendors charging absurd amounts of money "just because they can".  I don't know what's going on in Brazil, but it could be something like that.<br /><br />If you ever want something from the US, let me know -- I ship stuff out internationally fairly often.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Fri Aug 13, 2010 4:35 pm</p><hr />
